# Auto-Generated REST API using LoopBack 4

## Tool Used
**LoopBack 4** -

## API Features
- Full CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
- RESTful endpoints
- Interactive API Explorer
- Built-in validation
- In-memory database


## Book Model Schema
```typescript
{
  id: number (auto-generated)
  title: string (required)
  author: string (required)
  year: number (optional)
}


## Steps Followed to Generate the API

### 1. Install LoopBack CLI
```bash
npm install -g @loopback/cli
```

### 2. Create Application
```bash
lb4 app
```
- Project name: books-api
- Selected all recommended features

### 3. Generate Model
```bash
lb4 model
```
- Created "Book" entity with properties: id, title, author, year, genre

### 4. Generate DataSource
```bash
lb4 datasource
```
- Created in-memory database datasource

### 5. Generate Repository
```bash
lb4 repository
```
- Created BookRepository connected to the datasource

### 6. Generate Controller
```bash
lb4 controller
```
- Created REST controller with CRUD operations
- Auto-generated all API endpoints

## Running the API

### Install Dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### Start the Server
```bash
npm start
```

The API will be available at `http://localhost:3000`
